"{\"uid\": \"promptnewsonline.com-2024-olympic-qualifier-onumonu-reveals-super-falcons-ambition-ahead-cameroon-clash\", \"text\": \"  By Obaloluwa Joshua, LAGOS  Ifeoma Onumonu believes the Super Falcons have what it takes to earn a berth at the 2024 Olympic Games.  The West Africans are looking to make a return to the Olympics after a 16-year absence.  Randy Waldrum's side started their qualifying campaign with a comprehensive victory against Ethiopia in the second round.  The Super Falcons will face perennial rivals Indomitable Lionesses of Cameroon in the first leg of their third qualifying round tie on Friday.  The encounter is slated for the Stade de la Reunification, Douala.READ ALSO:  \\\"I am really confident of our qualification because I think we have a good team, we are together and we are prepared, and I think we are going to beat this team both away and in our home, no disrespect to them though,\\\" Onumonu toldpainmedia.com.  \\\"I want to promise we are going to be at this year's Olympics, I mean we have not been there for years, so that is our real number one goal, anything can happen in this game, but our focus right now is to beat Cameroon\\\"    Comments are closed.    Prompt News Online is published by PNO Dynamic Media Limited.  Address:Suite 24, Abebi Plaza, Oluseyi, Sango - Eleyele Road, Ibadan, Oyo State, Nigeria.  Managing Editor/CEO:Akeem Oyetunji  Email:[email\\u00a0protected]or[email\\u00a0protected]  Phone/WhatsApp:+234806 286 2057Or 0805 386 6284  Type above and pressEnterto search. PressEscto cancel.\"}"